Lieutenant General Brent Scowcroft, a highly esteemed figure in the field of national security, has passed away. He served as the National Security Advisor for Presidents Gerald Ford and George H.W. Bush, and played a significant role in shaping the modern role of the NSA. Known for his effective leadership and commitment to providing well-vetted policy options and advice, Scowcroft acted as an "honest broker" in his position. The current National Security Advisor, who greatly admires Scowcroft, aims to follow his example in serving President Trump's NSC. The statement expresses condolences to Scowcroft's family and celebrates his life and dedicated service to the country.